                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1120</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Tiflis</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-20T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 12, 10 p.m. British military agent, Caucasus, reports to his
                    Government that three Americans were recently in Tiflis who proposed to
                    subsidize Georgia with view to declaration of autonomy.</p>
                <p>Advise Department fully and promptly facts of this report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
